<subSubSection pageId="62" pageNumber="63" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,1334,2020]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1892,1916]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is one of the larger agalliine leafhoppers of the 
<collectingRegion box="[940,1116,1892,1916]" country="Oman" name="Shamal ash Sharqiyah" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Oriental region</collectingRegion>
, others being 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[1281,1405,1892,1916]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="violacea">I. violacea</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurora">I. aurora</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Osborn)" authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[282,506,1926,1950]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis box="[282,394,1926,1950]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">I. fasciata</emphasis>
(Osborn)
</taxonomicName>
. It can be readily recognised by the coloration and male genitalia. It closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="C.A.Viraktamath, 2011" authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[203,303,1962,1985]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurora" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[203,303,1962,1985]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">I. aurora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[310,399,1961,1985]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[310,399,1961,1985]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="C.A.Viraktamath, 2011" authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[454,581,1961,1985]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delineata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[454,581,1961,1985]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">I. delineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[588,678,1961,1985]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[588,678,1961,1985]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(see below) but differs from the former in the structure of the style, subgenital plate and from the latter in the structure of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
